#!N 
#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rrcpa Restricting Control Panel Access #!N 
#!EC #!N #!N Access to Control Panels is restricted using the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control Panel Access... #!EF dialog box. This dialog box is 
opened by selecting the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control Panel Access #!EF in the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Option #!EF menu of the VPE, Image, or Control Panel 
windows. The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control Panel Access #!EF dialog is used to 
restrict certain Control Panel names or Control Panel groups names from 
appearing in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Open Control Panel by Name #!EF option 
in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Windows #!EF window. #!N #!N A  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control 
Panel Access #!EF dialog box appears in  #!Lprogmx84,dxall406 f Figure 84  #!EL  . #!Cbrown #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rprogmx84 #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the 
manual. #!N #!N Figure 84. Control Panel Access Dialog Box #!EF 
#!N #!EC Each Control Panel and Control Panel group is listed. 
To the left of each is a toggle button. This toggle 
button is used to select which Control Panels or groups can 
be accessed from the window in which the dialog box was 
opened. To the right of the Control Panel names is an 
ellipsis toggle. (Note that Control Panel groups do not have the 
ellipsis.) The ellipsis toggle is used to open (or raise) the 
corresponding Control Panel when the button is activated. Once activated, selecting 
the button again closes the Control Panel and pops up the 
button. #!N #!N To restrict Control Panel access: #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Click on each Control Panel 
access toggle button that you wish to exclude so that those 
toggle buttons are deactivated. (Initially, all the toggle buttons are activated.) 
#!N #!I30 #!N 2. Once you have indicated which Control Panels 
and Control Panel groups you wish to exclude, click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
OK #!EF . #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N Selecting 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Cancel #!EF pushbutton causes the dialog box to be 
closed and any changes to be canceled. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   
